ENTRY 3: HERD & AGENT DATA EXTRACTION UTILITY
================================================================================

CSI ID: BISS-AUTO-2026-003

Improvement Summary:
HerdAgentExtractor & TestDataFactory Utility — Built a dedicated data 
extraction and generation library (HerdAgentExtractor.java, TestDataFactory.java) 
that automatically queries live Oracle databases (BISS_DATA + BISS_INET), selects 
valid herds with clean records, resolves owning agent logins, and mints unique 
test data on demand (emails, IDs, timestamps). Eliminates manual Excel-based 
test data management. Implemented smart shuffling (Random seeded by nanoTime) so 
no two runs select the same herd. Built blacklist enforcement (BLACKLISTED_HERDS 
set) and expired-agent tracking (EXPIRED_AGENTS set, populated at runtime when 
SSO fails). Provides fallback re-fetch with escalating DB limits 
(10 → 15 → 20 → 25 candidates per attempt).

Problem / Opportunity:
Legacy Manual Process: Before each test run, someone had to manually identify 
valid herds from a spreadsheet, check if agents were active, and paste them into 
the test files. Herds were consumed mid-run, forcing ad-hoc restarts. If a herd 
was blacklisted (already submitted, data issues, etc.), testers had to manually 
find a replacement. Test data was scattered across Excel, environment files, and 
hardcoded values. No tracking of which herds were expired or which logins were 
stale.

Opportunity: Automate the entire data-selection workflow so it runs in <5 
seconds at startup, never picks a bad herd, and self-recovers on failure.

Suggested Action:
Build Java utility to query BISS_DATA for "herds with no errors this year"; 
cross-check with BISS_INET for active agent logins; shuffle randomly; enforce 
blacklist; track expired agents; implement fallback re-fetch on failure; generate 
unique emails/IDs on demand via TestDataFactory; integrate with @BeforeAll hook 
so data is resolved before any scenario runs.

Status: ✅ Complete (February 2026) — Utility live, used by all test modules

Owner: Aniket Pathare (QA Automation Engineer)

Date Raised: 2026-01-20

Target Date: 2026-02-28

Outcome / Notes:
HerdAgentExtractor used by all 50+ test scenarios (BISS main, ENTS, Staff 
portal). Blacklist grows as herds are consumed; on next run, those herds are 
automatically skipped. Expired-agent set prevents re-login attempts on 
known-expired SSO accounts. Framework now self-sufficient; testers never touch 
data files.

TIME SAVED: 2–3 hours/sprint
Eliminates manual spreadsheet maintenance and herd validation. 5-second 
automated startup vs. 15–20 minute manual data prep. Automatic re-fetch on 
failure removes "go find another herd" manual debugging. No more test 
interruptions due to consumed herds or stale logins.

Innovation Highlights:
• Zero manual data entry — DBRouter + HerdAgentExtractor queries live DBs automatically
• Smart shuffling — nanoTime-seeded Random so no two runs repeat herds
• Blacklist enforcement — known-bad herds skipped automatically (BLACKLISTED_HERDS set)
• Expired-agent tracking — SSO failures trigger Hooks.markAgentExpired(), agent auto-excluded
• Escalating fallback — if first 10 herds don't work, re-fetch with limit 15 → 20 → 25
• Unique data generation — TestDataFactory mints emails, IDs, timestamps on demand
• HikariCP pooling — connection pooling eliminates DB connection startup delays


